---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Mission Profile">
    <section class="hero">
        <div class="container">
            <div style="font-family: 'Share Tech Mono', monospace; color: var(--accent-gold); letter-spacing: 4px; margin-bottom: 20px;">[ SECTOR: INTEL // DCO-550 ]</div>
            <h1>MISSION <span class="accent">PROFILE</span></h1>
            <p style="font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 800px; margin: 20px auto;">
                Bridging the gap between operational expertise and advanced technical implementation.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="container" style="padding: 80px 0;">
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 60px; align-items: flex-start;">
            <div>
                <h2 style="color: var(--accent-green); margin-top: 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding-bottom: 10px;">The Methodology</h2>
                <p style="font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.8;">
                    DCO 550 is a capstone-level offensive-defensive curriculum. It transitions operators from passive monitoring to proactive hunting by leveraging the <strong>Hunter's Triad</strong>:
                </p>
                
                <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 30px;">
                    <div style="padding: 20px; border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-green); background: rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.02);">
                        <h4 style="margin: 0; color: var(--accent-green);">I. DEEP FORENSICS</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 0;">Mastering artifact recovery from memory, NTFS, and the Registry to find the "unseen" footprints of an adversary.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="padding: 20px; border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-blue); background: rgba(0, 210, 255, 0.02);">
                        <h4 style="margin: 0; color: var(--accent-blue);">II. REVERSE ENGINEERING</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 0;">Dissecting malicious payloads to understand C2 protocols, anti-analysis triggers, and hidden logic.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="padding: 20px; border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-gold); background: rgba(255, 204, 0, 0.02);">
                        <h4 style="margin: 0; color: var(--accent-gold);">III. DATA SCIENCE</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 0;">Building Python-driven ETL pipelines to scale detection logic across enterprise datasets using statistical modeling.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card" style="border-color: var(--accent-green);">
                <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 25px;">
                    <div style="width: 80px; height: 80px; background: var(--bg-dark); border: 2px solid var(--accent-green); border-radius: 50%; margin: 0 auto 15px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-user-shield" style="font-size: 32px; color: var(--accent-green);"></i>
                    </div>
                    <h3 style="margin: 0;">Iver Iverson</h3>
                    <div style="font-family: 'Share Tech Mono', monospace; color: var(--text-dim); font-size: 12px; margin-top: 5px;">COMMANDER // DCO-550</div>
                </div>
                
                <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6;">
                    Iver is a defensive cyber operations professional with extensive experience in enterprise threat hunting and detection engineering.
                </p>
                <div style="font-family: 'Share Tech Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--accent-green);">
                    <div style="margin-bottom: 5px;">[ CERTIFICATIONS ]</div>
                    <div style="color: var(--text-secondary);">GCFA // GREM // GDAT</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
